The paper discusses random linear estimation with Gaussian measurement matrices and noise, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of the minimum mean-square error also suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.MM). The paper also introduces a new interpolation method, which could be relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
